description: From Middle English [Term?], from Old French endosser. Doublet of endorse.

verbs.description: endoss (third-person singular simple present endosses, present participle endossing, simple past and past participle endossed)

entries.meaning: (obsolete, transitive) To write on the back of (a document); to endorse.
(obsolete, transitive) To inscribe; to depict on any surface.
